<detall><id label=""><![CDATA[105753]]></id><title label="Titol"><![CDATA[The story of homeless people in the form of a portrait]]></title><excerpt label="Resum"><![CDATA[<strong>Exhibitions.</strong> The 'Retrats Sense Sostre' (Homeless Portraits) project tells the story of homeless people's lives through art.]]></excerpt><content label="Contingut"><![CDATA[<p>The artistic portraits and story of the lives of 12 homeless people will be displayed in various parts of the city from 13 to 30 November. They are part of the &#8220;Retrats Sense Sostre&#8221; project, which aims to speak for homeless people through art, research and communication. For this, 12 artists have spent time with homeless people to do a portrait of them. Each one is the result of conversations and meetings between the artists and the subjects of the portraits.</p>
